description: Jack "King" Kirby's Silver Star is collected in full color at last! Chronicling the rise of Homo-Geneticus, the New Breed of humanity that spawns both Silver Star and the nefarious Darius Brumm, Silver Star was Kirby's final creation and one of only two creator-owned projects published by Pacific Comics in the early '80s. Featuring lovingly reconstructed color work, this deluxe hardcover is a must-have for any Kirby fan!
name: HC

description: Â Image Comics' archival collections of Jack "King" Kirby's creator-owned work for Pacific Comics continue with Captain Victory and the Galactic Rangers! Featuring lovingly reconstructed color work, this deluxe hardcover chronicles the adventures of Captain Victory and his unique crew of galactic rangers as they battle such foes as Lightning Lady, the Wonder Warriors and the ominous Blackmass. A must-have for any Kirby Collector!
name: HC

description: Based on the all-new animated series! Join CLIFFJUMPER and ARCEE as they battle their way through DECEPTICON forces in a desperate adventure to learn the secrets of Space Bridge Technology! STARSCREAM, the DECEPTICON enforcer stands in their way, not just from the mission, but to rejoin OPTIMUS PRIME and his AUTOBOTS as well! This is the PREQUEL to the new hit TV Show!

Emperor Kurr vs. Virus in the battle to end all battles: Whoever wins - we lose! Emperor Kurr's master plan is executed at last! Death! Destruction! It's a cataclysmic conclusion of biblical proportions - Old Testament - real wrath of God type stuff! The world goes through its death throes as the whole damned human races comes to a screeching halt! It's unlike anything you've ever read or imagined! It's the most mind-blowing finale in the history of comics! This is the big one! It's the end of the world as we know it!
name: Emperor Dragon, Part Eight: This Ravaged World

description:
Jedi Kerra Holt prevented the destruction of the mining colony of Chelloa . . . but she also began a Sith--on--Sith war, and the colony is in the middle!

Complete annihilation has not come to the planet of Chelloa by the hand of Sith Lord Odion, but a war between him and his rival brother, Lord Daiman, might not leave much of the planet for either of them to rule. It's up to Kerra to find the advantage in the rivalry between the two Sith.
name: Aflame Part 4 of 5

description: This special issue of Flare Adventures was released for Free Comic Book Day 2005. It features adventures of Flare, the Black Enchantress and Psyche. Cover by Frank Brunner!
name: Challenge of the Whipperette

description: For the first time in color, enjoy Chapters Two and Three of Flare's classic "Adventure in Olympus." Cover by Frank Brunner!
name: Adventures In Olympus, Chapter Two: Glitter

description: Relive Flare's very first encounter with the savage Tigress. Also in this issue, it's the debut of Commander Fantastic and the All-Girl Hero League.
name: Flare Vs. The Tigress

description: It's the cataclysmic showdown between the forces of light and darkness when Flare does battle with the night-goddess Nyx. Also in this issue, Britannia stars in "The Maid and the Rogue." Originally published as Flare Vol. 2 #15.
name: Sigma-Chi, Master Of Claus Fu

description: Enjoy Chapter Four of Flare's classic adventure in Olympus, plus an all-new adventure of Commander Fantastic and the All-Girl Hero League.
name: Return To Olympus

description: In this issue, while Lady Arcane and the Black Enchantress work on trying to bring her back, Flare's adventures in Olympus continue as she gets ready for a showdown with her arch-enemy Nyx, goddess of the light. Also in this issue, a classic confrontation between Lady Arcane and the Black Enchantress.
name: Olympian Magic

description: It's Flare vs the night goddess Nyx in the thrilling conclusion to the "Flare in Olympus" storyline. Plus an adventure from out of the past, when Flare was a girl growing up in the Amazon.
name: The Battle Between Night And Day

description: It's an all-new blast from the past as we travel back to the days when Flare was a girl growing up in the jungles of the Amazon to witness "The Death of Fala," by Dennis Mallonee and Jeff Tompkins. Also in this issue, for the first time in color, the savage original TIGRESS gets ready for her second encounter with our glittering goddess of the light in the classic tale, "The Return of the Tigress," by Dennis Mallonee, Paul Abrams, and John Tighe.
name: The Death Of Fala

description: In this 24th issue of Flare Adventures, writer Dennis Mallonee and artist Paul Abrams present "The Revenge of the Tigress." When the savage TIGRESS swaps bodies with FLARE, our glittering heroine finds herself in a heap of trouble, and it may be that not even LADY ARCANE will be able to help her put things to right. Also in this issue, the naughty Black Enchantress stars in the classic adventure, "What Every Boy Wants," by Dennis Mallonee and Howard Simpson. All this, plus three new pages from the Flare Sunday newspaper strip, by Dennis Mallonee and Sean Harrington.
name: The Revenge Of The Tigress

description: For the first time in color! It's the cataclysmic 26-page conclusion to the classic adventure, "Flare Versus the Tigress," by Dennis Mallonee and Paul Abrams! Also in this issue, enjoy a special bonus treat with two Flare Sunday pages by Dennis Mallonee and Tim Burgard.
name: There's A New Tigress In Town

description: When comics' glittering goddess of light meets up with the world's sexiest spy, it's time to go SPYING WITH LANA! In this booklength crossover epic, enjoy a SEAN HARRINGTON tour de force as he brings two of his favorite females together for the very first time. WARNING: There is nudity in this issue. But it's way cool.
name: Flare Goes Spying With Lana

description: The classic six-part crossover adventure between the League of Champions and the Southern Knights is being presented in color for the very first time! And of course FLARE plays a part in it. In Flare Adventures #27, Flare teams up with her good friend Icicle, and Dragon of the Southern Knights, as they find themselves caught in "A Past Not Their Own," in what seems to be Atlanta in the year 1768. But how can that be? In the world we know, Atlanta wasn't even founded until 1837! Clearly, there's something very strange going on. And unless answers can be found, there may not be a future for them to return to. This is Part Three of "The Morrigan Wars," a book-length, 26-page adventure, with story by Henry Vogel and Dennis Mallonee, artwork by Howard Bender and Mark Propst.
name: The Morrigan Wars Part 3: A Past Not Their Own

description:
The classic six-part crossover adventure between the League of Champions and the Southern Knights is being presented in color for the very first time! And of course FLARE plays a part in it. But the Flare who appears in Flare Adventures #28, is not the Flare we know!

When the Huntsman finds himself appearing "One Day in Future's Past," in the year 2097 with Aramis and Kristin of the Southern Knights, Flare is there, too. But it isn't Terri Feran. It's Sabrina Martel, the Flare of the future! And the world of 2097 is a world fans of our classic science fiction hero ETERNITY SMITH will find very familiar, a world in which mankind stands on the brink of extermination, fighting a hopeless war against an army of thinking machines.

This is Part Five of "The Morrigan Wars," a book-length, 26-page adventure, with story by Henry Vogel and Dennis Mallonee, artwork by Gordon Purcell, Joe Martin, and Jeff Brennan. You'll find Parts One, Two, Four, and Six in Champions #47-50, and Part Three in Flare Adventures #27.

Also in this issue, a bonus Flare Sunday page by Dennis Mallonee and Mark Beachum.
name: The Morrigan Wars Part 5: One Day In Future's Past

description: Daoun is a young, ambitious woman in her first year of teaching high school. Handsome, dark and mysterious, "prince charming" Ryumin flunked his senior year and is a student in her class with a devastating crush on his teacher. And Hyunwoo, a former classmate and fellow teacher of Daoun's, has been in love with her for years but doesn't have the courage to tell her. As Ryumin's advancements toward Daoun increase and Hyunwoo starts to notice, will Daoun follow her head or her heart?
name: Vol. 1

description: The course of love is never smooth for new teacher Daoun Jung. Although her class continues to resist her, the coolly handsome Ryumin becomes altogether too friendly. And he's not the only one revealing more. Hayoung and shy Hyunwoo are also trying to come out on top of high school's most complicated love triangle. It's all inside the scandalous second volume of Seduction More Beautiful Than Love.
name: Vol. 2

description:
Grizzly cub Toklo dreams of one day being a great big bear who will rule the forest. He will mark his wide territory and hunt the biggest game, and his brother, Tobi, will forever be at his side. Other grizzlies may stalk the forest alone, but Toklo and Tobi will always have each other.

Yet for now, they're too little to defend themselves, and when a terrifying grizzly demands they leave his territoryâor elseâthey have no choice but to abandon the only home they've ever known. Will Toklo be able to help his family find a new homeâor will he just get them into even greater trouble?
name: Toklo's Story

description: After his home world is ruthlessly taken over by the Abh--a space-faring race that has conquered thousands of galaxies--a boy named Jinto begins an unforgettable journey that stretches the boundaries of the final frontier. With a beautiful princess at his side, he will attempt to unlock the secret behind the Abh domination and discover that all's fair in love and interplanetary war.
name: Crest of the Stars

description: Three years have passed since Lafiel and Jinto escape from Planet Sufugnoff. Lafiel is now captain of her own Assault Ship, the Basroil, and has requested the services of Jinto Lin as supply officer. The conflict between Humankind Empire Abh and the Triple Alliance has entered one of its hottest phases as the Abh initiate Operation Phantom Flame to capture a huge swath of enemy territory. Even as Lafiel must deal with the pressures of command, Jinto works to make himself worthy of his Empire and of Lafiel's friendship. In the meantime, both are haunted by a phantom from the past and menaced by an numerically superior enemy fleet.
name: Banner of the Stars

description: With the success of Operation Phantom Flame, the Abh Empire is now in control of vast amounts of territory once controlled by its enemy, the United Mankind. As the Empire begins a new operation to mop up the remaining resistance, Lafiel and Jinto find themselves placed in the role of Territorial Ambassadors on the planet of Lobnas II. The Abh find dealing with surface worlds distasteful enough, but complicating matters further is the fact that Lobnas II is a prison planet whose population disagrees on the best future for their newly liberated world. When the United Mankind returns in an attempt to reclaim Lobnas, an angry revolt leaves Jinto stranded in the chaos. Lafiel must decide choosing rescuing the man who has been her advisor and friend or saving her ship from the oncoming enemy fleet.
name: Banner of the Stars II

description:
Masayoshi must come to grips with his identity, all the while fighting off legions of ghosts--the remnants of men killed by Oni-hime!

First to Fifth Night.
name: Vol. 1

description: When Oni-hime's father plans to retrieve Oni-hime, he calls upon four powerful warriors who swore loyalty to evil in the past life. These warriors can summon magic and change their bodily forms, and have fought many fierce and grueling battles. How can Masayoshi kill someone who's already dead? He must act fast if he is to discover the truth behind Oni-hime's deal with the devil before the restless spirits enact their vengeance. The finale to Sengoku Nights erupts in a chilling, bloody climax!
name: Vol. 2

description:
As punishment for being late to class, Kanata has to ring a bell in an old, deserted church near his high school. When the floor breaks, Kanata falls into a vast room, where he discovers a coffin--and inside, the body of a vampire. The vampire rises, killing Kanata. But Kanata's soul is saved, and when he later meets the vampire, they realize that they are bound to each other through a magic spell: If Kanata dies, the vampire dies, too!

Story 1 - 6.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Close Encounters of the Green Kind! Sgt. Keroro, commanding officer of Planet Keron's invasion force, has a problem. After blowing his cover and losing his top-secret weapon, the frog-like alien has been cut off from his homeworld. To make matters worse, he's lost communications with the rest of his platoon. Now he has taken cover in the Hinata family household, where in exchange for doing his share of the chores, he gets his own room from which to secretly devise new plans for world domination!

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter I: Enter the Sergeant!
  • Encounter II: An Audience With General Mom
  • Encounter III: Me, Myself and Momoko
  • Encounter IV: The Sarge's Quarters - Invasion From Within!
  • Encounter V: Cohabitation of the Third Kind
  • Encounter VI: Alien Observation Journal
  • Encounter 6.5: (6.5 Haunted Houseguest)
  • Encounter VII: Carnage In the Storm
  • Encounter VIII: Momoko's South Seas Operation
  • Encounter IX: Extended Shore Leave
  • Encounter X: Behold the Lord of Terror! Apocalypse Now!
  • Bonus: Sergeant Frog Unveiled
  • Bonus: The Monster Files: 01
name: Vol. 1

description:
Gun-toting, Mutinous Frogs! It's the dawn of a new school year for Fuyuki Hinata. As if the stress of starting junior high weren't enough, he must also deal with Sgt. Keroro--the froglike alien with apocalyptic intentions--freeloading in his attic. But if Fuyuki thought the Sergeant was a handful, wait'll he gets a load of the rest of the battalion. Members of the Sarge's lost platoon are starting to surface like a plague of frogs, and not all of them agree with the way that Keroro's been running the invasion. When the gun-crazy Corporal Giroro sees the pampered pet that his superior officer has become, will he take control of the mission?

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter XI: A New Life-Form Attacks!
  • Encounter XII: Battle Royale: Keroro vs. Giroro
  • Encounter XIII:Sergeant Raches the Critical Point
  • Encounter XIV: Top Secret Operations Rally!!
  • Encounter XV: Momoka's Love: A Narrow Escape!
  • Encounter XVI: The Hinatas Ring In A Clean New Year
  • Encounter XVII: Operation: Relative Interception!
  • Encounter XVIII: Operation: Chocolate Shock!
  • Encounter XIX: The 623 Incident!!
  • Encounter XX: A Fourth Visitor
  • Bonus: All About Private Tamama
  • Bonus: All About Corporal Giroro
  • Bonus: Encounter 20.5: Danger! Earth Soldier!!
name: Vol. 2

description:
Science and Technology are truly miraculous things -- except when in the hands of a super-genius super-jerk like the Keroro Platoon's recently recovered tactical officer, Sergeant Major Kululu. Already, Kululu is developing biochemical weapons that no Earth medicine can combat, and rays that can turn the entire planet into helpless children! But where can a fugitive alien find test subjects for such diabolical weapons? Where indeed but the Hinata household! Meanwhile, Private Tamama and Angol Moa vie for the Sergeant's affections, Momoka vies for Fuyuki's affections, Natsumi enters a swimsuit competition, and a frog of the fairer sex appears on the scene...

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter XXI: Welcome To Radio-Free Keroro
  • Encounter XXII: Natsumi's Number Is Up
  • Encounter XXIII: General Mom's Charge To Relive Her Youth
  • Encounter XXIV: Operation: Swimsuit Issue
  • Encounter XXV: A Horror Showdown!
  • Encounter XXVI: Lady Moa Grows Up Fast
  • Encounter XXVII: Enter the Other Momoka!
  • Encounter XXVIII: Momoka Platoon Strikes Back
  • Encounter XXIX: A Very Keroro Christmas
  • Bonus Encounter: Sumomo: A Mission of Love
name: Vol. 3

description:
The Keroro Platoon rings in the New Year with a bang--and has the hangover to prove it. But underneath the scandal of a liquidly courageous Lady Moa revealing her true feelings for the Sergeant...underneath the threat of a jealous Tamama laying the ultimate smackdown...underneath the Hinata family's inevitable discovery of the mess...is something else. Someone the platoon has completely forgotten. Its fifth member.

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter XXX: True Confessions! A Shocking New Year
  • Encounter XXXI: The Revenge of the Red Goblin!!
  • Encounter XXXII: To the Death!! The First Snowball Fight
  • Encounter XXXIII: The Sergeant Gets What He Deserves
  • Encounter XXXIV: Number Three Molar: The Devils Residence!!
  • Encounter XXXV: I Am You and You Are Me
  • Encounter XXXVI: Incoming! Keroro Platoons Number One Fan
  • Encounter XXXVII: A Hinata Family Reunion

Bonus Encounters

  • Encounter 30.5: Letters From th Homeworld
  • Encounter 37.5: Riding Paul
name: Vol. 4

description:
What sinister plans do these amphibian fibbers have hiding under their lily pads?! Luring Earthlings to hot springs so that they relax uselessly -- to their doom?! Crashing the school sports festival...just for fun? A thrilling game of Parcheesi, where the winner gets Pokopen? The answer is: All of this and more! And in the end, there's nothing like the warmth of the spring sun to make everyone feel a little mellow.

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter XXXVIII: Beat the Heat! Attack From Below!!
  • Encounter XXXIX: Operation: Crash the Sports Festival!!
  • Encounter XL: Operation: Dazzle the Heavenly Hosts!!
  • Encounter XLI: Operation: Birthday Blitz!!
  • Encounter XLII: Operation: New Year's Parcheesi!!
  • Encounter XLIII: Momoka Goes Awol? The Father Descends!!
  • Encounter XLIV: Lord of Terror, Go! Go! Go!
  • Encounter XLV: Back To the Subject--Forward March!!
  • Bonus Encounter 45.5: The Monsters of the Hinata Family
name: Vol. 5

description:
It's an intergalactic battle for the planet when Keroro and company come under attack by a mysterious man and his sidekick. Will our fearless froggy fighters be able to hold down their lily pads? Later, an inexplicable order from the higher ups makes Tamama the new general! The maniacal mutant mutiny continues as someone steals Giroro's trusty belt...leaving him caught with his pants down!

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter XLVI: Target: The Hinata Home!!
  • Encounter XLVII: A Motion For Demotion?!
  • Encounter XLVIII: Water Battle: Natsumi vs. Frog!!
  • Encounter XLIX: Danger In the Deep Sea!!
  • Encounter L: Matsuri Battle: Alien vs. Iron Man!!
  • Encounter LI: A Jerk And A Genius! The Legend Of A Sergeant-Major
  • Encounter LII: Feelings All the Way! The Legend of A Corporal
  • Encounter LIII: The World's Smallest Invasion: Part 1
  • Bonus: Special Stand-Alone Issue: Sergeant Keroro
name: Vol. 6

description:
When Koyuki, a new student, instantly falls in love with Natsumi, the secret of the Hinata family might be in jeopardy! The new student is actually a special agent who must report back to the Fifth One. Koyuki moves in next door with the hopes of getting a glimpse of the real family dirt!

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter LIV: The World's Smallest Invasion: Continued
  • Encounter LV: Enter the Dragonlike Transfer Student!
  • Encounter LVI: The Fifth One Appears! The Legend of Dororo
  • Encounter LVII: Emergency Warning! Koyuki Azumaya Approaching!!
  • Encounter LVIII: Invasion In Bloom!! Operation: Cosmic Flower Expo!
  • Encounter LIX: Special Effects: Job Hunting Made Simple!!
  • Encounter LX: A Spreading Contagion?! Runaway May Disease!
  • Encounter LXI: Swallow This! An Annual Invasion

Bonus Encounters

  • Big Bonus 1
  • Encounter 54.5: The World's Smallest Invasion: The Lost Episode
name: Vol. 7

description:
The sergeant's biggest menace has been Natsumi, Earth's first line of defense. When Sgt. Keroro finally discovers her weakness, it's up to Fuyuki to defend Earth. And...why haven't the Keron Troops invaded Pokopen? It's because they lack the manpower, of course! Never one to waste an opportunity, Keroro is off to the zoo to recruit reinforcements for his platoon and he takes Kururu's latest invention with him!

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter LXII: Natsumi In Crisis! A New Biological Weapon!
  • Encounter LXIII: Power Outage! Operation: Beat the Heat!
  • Encounter LXIV: Body Alteration! Operation: Door-To-Door Sales
  • Encounter LXV: Impulse Buy! My Poorly Maintained Wings!
  • Encounter LXVI: Operation: Hijack--Manga-Writer Style!
  • Encounter LXVII: The Charge of the Animal Brigade!
  • Encounter LXVIII: Media Attack! Operation: Welcoming Party!
  • Encounter LXIX: For Today's Youth: A Dose of Cold, Harsh Reality
name: Vol. 8

description:
Frogs Gone Wild Hot springs resorts, Children's Day and monsoons drive the Keroro Platoon to the extreme! When Keroro is left home alone, Fuyuki's innocent Children's Day decorations become weapons for the sergeant. When Fuyuki finds out, not even Natsumi can stop this outraged Hinata on a rampage! During the monsoon season, Keroro has to use a power limiter or else he loses all control. When they try removing the limiter, the frog goes haywire! And when the Platoon is about to be sent back to Keron for taking too long to conquer Earth, Kururu has a plan to fool them all--an Earth replica operation!

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter LXX: Operation: Avaricious Mixed Bathing!!
  • Encounter LXXI: Fish Battle!! Invasion Will Be Child's Play!!!
  • Encounter LXXII: The Eve of the 623 Incident!
  • Encounter LXXIII: Earth! Hairball!! Entanglement!!!
  • Encounter LXXIV: Rain, Then Encounter, Then Separation, Then Sun
  • Encounter LXXV: An Invasion of Convenience?
  • Encounter LXXVI: Forbidden Planet? Super-Secret Operation!!
  • Bonus Encounters: Encounter 74.5: And Further Beyond...
name: Vol. 9

description:
As Earth is anesthetized by Planet Anesthesia, the only mobile people left are the members of Keron Forces and those close to Keroro. One by one, Keroro Platoon members are silenced and their friends are eliminated! Natsumi tries to defend Earth but is foiled by Tororo. Will no one save Earth before its inhabitants are silenced forever?

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter LXXVII: Bloodcurdling Fright: A Battle of Spirits and Space!--Part One
  • Encounter LXXVIII: Bloodcurdling Fright: A Battle of Spirits and Space!--Part Two
  • Encounter LXXIX: A Lesson in Alien Savoir Faire!
  • Encounter LXXX: Fuyuki Hinata's Alien Lifestyle Report
  • Encounter LXXXI: The Last Battle: Keroro Platoon's 24 Hours--Part One
  • Encounter LXXXII: The Last Battle: Keroro Platoon's 24 Hours--Part Two
  • Encounter LXXXIII: The Last Battle: Keroro Platoon's 24 Hours--Part Three
  • Bonus Encounter: Power Natsumi: The Authoritative Guide!
name: Vol. 10

description: The bloody conclusion of the ten-issue vampire epic on the bayou from the writer of the A Song of Ice and Fire novels! From the New York Times Best-selling author, George R. R. Martin, comes a tale of vampire clans, death and debauchery, legendary blood masters, and even a few epic steamboat races on the muddy Mississippi. This is Martin's FEVRE DREAM, an antebellum story of power, loss, and the fever of bloodlust. It's been years since Abner Marsh has seen his old friend and co-captain, Joshua. The Civil War has come and gone, and new steamboats sail on rivers whose names have changed. And that, Marsh supposes, should have been the end of that. But Damon Julian is readying for a new war, and Joshua must ask for Abner's help one last time -- to save him, and the world! This is the final showdown, and not everyone will survive the conclusion! Each issue of this stunning full-color epic is illustrated by Rafa Lopez, an artist whose skilled line captures every moonlit drop of blood in delicious detail. Adapted by the Hugo-nominated author Daniel Abraham, this version of FEVRE DREAM stays faithful to Martin's original dark vision, while bringing the torture and joy of his vampires to almost-human life...

volume.name: George R. R. Martin's Fevre Dream

description:
Lieutenant Garuru--Girororo's ruthless older brother--has taken command of the Space Invasion Force and has stripped Keroro of his rank! Adding insult to injury, Garuru has unleashed a plan to revert Keroro back to a tadpole. Luckily, Fuyuki has the Kero Ball! Can he use it to save Keroro...and the Earth?

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter LXXXIV: The Last Battle: Keroro Platoon's 24 Hours--Part Four
  • Encounter LXXXV: The Tale of Koyuki Azumaya & Dororo
  • Encounter LXXXVI: Battle of the Models Breaks Out At the Hinata Family Home
  • Encounter LXXXVII: Master Natsumi Rainy Rescue Operation
  • Encounter LXXXVIII: A New Beginning? A Determined Sergeant Leaves Home
  • Encounter LXXXIX: Pathos: Pokopen Fair Pavilion Construction Plan
  • Encounter LXXXX: A Real Hit?! Runaway Youth of the Keron Forces!!
  • Encounter LXXXXI: Operation: Pamper General Mom!
name: Vol. 11

description:
The invasion continues! Humanity's downfall is imminent! And Natsumi is in a real bad mood! When Keroro and Fuyuki deepen their friendship in the tub, Natsumi ends up feeling stuck in the shallow end. But Keroro comes down with a mysterious illness, and it looks like he won't make it! Will our amphibious invader finally croak?! Oh, c'mon--we're not gonna kill off our main characters just yet! Especially when we've got an adventure filled with a big-ass watermelon, a raucous Halloween party, and a jump-rope exhibition in space. With page after page of merry gambol and leaping adventure, it's enough to make you want to sleep through New Year's!

Chapter Titles

  • Encounter XCII: Strictly Forbidden: A Hard-Boiled Ban!
  • Encounter XCIII: Splendor In the Tub!
  • Encounter XCIV: Keroro Falls Ill: Chaos Ensues!
  • Encounter XCV: All Hail the Watermelon Generation!
  • Encounter XCVI: Crash! Typhoon Declares Victory!
  • Encounter XCVII: The First (And Last) All-Space Jump Rope Championship!
  • Encounter XCVIII: Trick Or Threat? A Halloween Invasion!
  • Encounter XCIX: Messengers From the Dark: Fuyuki's Rescue!
  • Encounter C: The Frog Who Lost new Year's!
  • Bonus Encounters: Encounter 100.5: A Door of Truth...!
name: Vol. 12

description: Keroro is back with another wacky episode. This time, some unruly visitors from Planet QQ are out to swindle Keroro for one of Earth's most prized possession--Natsumi! Will Natsumi be wisked away by these two-bit hustlers? Meanwhile, Keroro has a brief encounter with Momokaâs mother, Oka and Fuyuki-and it doesnât look good! Will the Sergeant and company finally take over the world?
name: Vol. 13

description: You smell it in the air and feel it in your bones. There's even a certain hop in your walk. Yes, indeed, summertime is finally here! But Keroro and the Hinata clan seem too busy to take notice of a little war of the worlds. As temperatures rise in the heat of battle, there's one cure for this group of hot heads: Soaking in a cool pool! Alas, there's just a little problem of shrinkage, and we don't mean from an alien member. So tune into your cosmic radio and broadcast to everyone you know--that giant sucking sound you hear is the latest in Keroro's new line of toys! But the question is: Will we all make it through this adventure without croaking?

Keroro's latest and greatest plan to conquer Earth takes a turn for the cunning, the corrupt, and...the cute?! When gang green transforms itself into a group of adorable little plushy versions of themselves, will those frog fatales finally take the upper webbed hand in the battle for the planet? It may take a friendly game of bowling to ultimately settle the score--just don't be suprised if Keroro ends up in the gutter. The madness and mayhem is enough to make you want hop and chew gum at the same time.

It's Christmas in Pokopen and Keroro wants to celebrate in a special way, but what to do? Spend a quiet evening by the fire? Defend the house from an invasion of super mice? Make gigantic snowmen to destroy all who stand in his way? Star in a new television show? Conquer Earth by turning himself into a 100-foot tall monster?! Let the festivities begin!!

In this prequel to "Multiple Personality Girl" - the story of Momoka Nishizawa just before she entered the world of Fuyuki and Keroro - "Dark Momoka" makes her first appearance when she sees Tamama being beaten up by an alien dog... Grrr! Also in this paper-cut-filled volume, as the sun hit high noon, Giroro discovers he's in too deep when a day at the beach turns into 20,000 Leagues Under the Sea. And somewhere in all this madness, Sgt. Frog comes up with another ingenious plan to get back at Natsumi. But will his bark be worse than his bite... Or will his scheme just downright suck?

Keroro and his friends are full of schemes to conquer the Earth, from training soldiers through karaoke to exploiting human reliance on cows to creating the perfect invasion environment with rain dolls! Looks like Keroro and his friends aren't the only ones planning to invade Earth, it turns out there's another alien force wrecking havoc with a monstrous new weapon! description: Nobu is a troubled teenager with a dark past. His old high school was sucked into the Underworld, where he and his fellow students battled hordes of demons led by the Demon Lord, Hazama. However, Nobu and a demon-possessed girl named Yumi managed to claw their way back to the Surface World, hoping to start new lives at new schools. But it isn't long before Nobu uncovers a government conspiracy to raise Hell on Earth, and he and Yumi are once again forced to face their worst nightmares...
